          "date": "2014-04-17 18:08:07.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "subject": "LU-4878 osd-ldiskfs: don't assert on possible upgrade",
        "message": "LU-4878 osd-ldiskfs: don't assert on possible upgrade\n\nThere are some cases possible during upgrade to the Lustre 2.5\nfrom older versions which need workaround instead assertion.\nMore generaly, this concerns any upgrade to a version that\ninclude Gerrit change #5049 from LU-2059:\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/5049\nLustre-commit: I137e38abb0e93c12406c6610c0922f4294e67290\n\nThe osd_object_ref_del() shouldn't assert on nlink == 0 if\nobject is local file but produce error message.\n\nThe underlying ext4_unlink() code doesn't treat decref on an\ninode with nlink == 0 as a fatal error either, so only print\nan error in the non-upgrade case for regular objects.\n\nThis patch is the b2_4 back-port of original/b2_5 version\nfrom Mike, in LU-3915 with Gerrit-Id #7673:\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/7673\nLustre-commit: I5aa1cc3d9a6d6210e8ce9f55193a4f25507b0986.\n\nSigned-off-by: Mikhail Pershin <mike.pershin@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: Bruno Faccini <bruno.faccini@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I28efb41a785778ed6dd99b730be7c46a938f23a7\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_4"
    }
  },
